sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45125
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: F-Plasmid OriT with Autolysin for Cell Death Induced Conjugation
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: OriT is the nic region on the F Plasmid that allows for conjugation in the presence of transfer genes encoded in TraJ genes. This OriT gene is followed by an autolysin N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanine amidase. This codes for an Autolysin that will cause cell death to the cell upon conjugation. This composite part is meant to be incorporated into a plasmid with the TraJ genes knocked out with a kanamycin resistance gene. This will further prevent conjugation by the bacteria.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sherissa Ward
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was made using an autolysin from Bacillus subtilis and other parts in the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There may need to be up-regulation of the autolysin in this case to increase the rate of cell death.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OriTF
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: OriT-F (Origin of Transfer for the F-plasmid nic region)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
OriTf (Origin of Transfer for the F-type conjugative plasmid) is the nic region, is where the relaxosome nicks the plasmid and conjugative transfer by F plasmid machinery begins via rolling circle replication.
This particular plasmid has been derived from a F-type plasmid donated by Professor Laura Frost University of Alberta.
NOTE: OriTf is NOT the same as the host cell's native Origin of Transfer (this is a separate site within the bacterial host's main genome).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Golden Bear
